Introduction¶



In this project, I am going to investigate and answer questions about The European soccer Database Which is a database contains data about The European Professional Football. It contains the data of 25k matches, 10k players, 11 European countries, and seasons from 2008 to 2016. 
I am going to investigate it through analysis using Python and Pandas. I am going to assess, clean, group, and visualize data. then interpret my findings.

The Questions I am going to search for an answers are:



  1. What is the most team achieved victories? 
  2. What team attributes lead to the most victories?

#function to discover and understand data
def discover_data(dataframe):
    print("\t\t\t\t\t\t----Data Frame data-----\n")
    print("##Dataframe shape:\n{}\n".format(dataframe.shape))
    print("##Dataframe info:\n{}\n".format(dataframe.info))
    print("##Dataframe data types\n:{}\n".format(dataframe.dtypes))
    print("##Dataframe nan sum\n:{}\n".format(dataframe.isna().sum()))
    print("##Dataframe duplicates sum:{}\n".format(dataframe.duplicated().sum()))
    print("##The top 5 rows in The DataFrame:")
    return dataframe.head()

    if row1 > row2 : 
        #condition when home team wins
        winning_team.append(df_match['home_team_api_id'].values[counter])
        lossing_team.append(df_match['away_team_api_id'].values[counter])

       
    elif row1 < row2: 
        #condition when away team wins
        winning_team.append(df_match['away_team_api_id'].values[counter])
        lossing_team.append(df_match['home_team_api_id'].values[counter])

    elif row1 == row2: 
        #condition when draw
        winning_team.append("draw")
        lossing_team.append("draw")
        
        
    counter+=1

#function to plot bar chart
def bar_plot(dataframe,x_axis,y_axis,title):
    sns.barplot(data=dataframe, x=x_axis,y=y_axis).set_title(title)

#function to plot scatter diagram
def scatter_plot(dataframe):
    sns.pairplot(data=dataframe).set_title(title)

#function to plot line chart
def line_plot(dataframe,x_axis_name,y_axis_name,title,hue=None):
    sns.lineplot(data=dataframe, x=x_axis_name, y=y_axis_name,hue=hue).set_title(title)
    
#function to plot scatter but only with two variables 
def xyscatter_plot(dataframe,x_axis_name,y_axis_name,title):
    sns.regplot(data=dataframe, x=x_axis_name, y=y_axis_name).set(title=title)

#function to plot box plot
def box_plot(dataframe,x_axis,title):
    sns.boxplot(data=dataframe, x=dataframe["{}".format(x_axis)]).set_title(title)

def hist_plot(dataframe,x_axis,title):
    sns.histplot(data=dataframe, x=x_axis, kde=True).set_title(title)
    
#function to increase plot size
def figsize(x,y):
    plt.figure(figsize=(x,y),dpi=80)

def pair_plot(dataframe,title,*keys):
    a= sns.pairplot(dataframe,x_vars=keys[0],y_vars=keys[1],kind="reg",plot_kws={'line_kws':{'color':'red'}},height=10,aspect=1.5)
    a.fig.suptitle(title,fontsize=50)
    a.fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.80) 
    return a

Answer to Question 2: the team attributes lead the most teams to achieve those victories?¶

Findings for this question deducted from the plots shows that "Defence Pressure", "Chance creation passing" are the two team attributes that lead to increase team victories, while decreasing the build up play plassing shows that win victories are increased

4. Conclusions¶

In Conclusion for this case study which is about analyzing European soccer Database from 2008 to 2016 to answer 
two questions: The most team achieved most victories over the time period and What are the attributes lead this team to achieve victories. 
From the plots, It has been shown that Barcelona -Named BAR on the plots- is the most team achieved victories by 234 Win . Real Madrid - Named REL on the plots - comes after Barcelona by achieving 228 Win.
In analyzing team attributes, It shows that for Barcelona defence pressure and defence team width was remarkably high from other teams so it must lead them to achieved those victories. and for Real Madrid chance creation shooting and chance creation passing was very high. 
In analyzing trends of win counts, lose counts, and goal counts, It's found that win counts increases when defence pressure and chance creation passing increases, and when build up play passing decreases
